  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "mailman security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for mailman is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2.",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Mailman is free software for managing electronic mail discussion and e-newsletter lists. Mailman is integrated with the web, making it easy for users to manage their accounts and for list owners to administer their lists. Mailman supports built-in archiving, automatic bounce processing, content filtering, digest delivery, spam filters, and more.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nIn GNU Mailman before 2.1.36, the CSRF token for the Cgi/admindb.py admindb page contains an encrypted version of the list admin password. This could potentially be cracked by a moderator via an offline brute-force attack.(CVE-2021-43332)\n\nIn GNU Mailman before 2.1.36, a crafted URL to the Cgi/options.py user options page can execute arbitrary JavaScript for XSS.(CVE-2021-43331)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for mailman is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "mailman",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
